{"article_id":"wYZ5Lej9wDAH1y2D","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Kavanaugh Supreme Court Confirmation Hearings Off To A Raucous Start","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Confirmation hearings for Supreme Court nominee Judge Brett Kavanaugh opened on a contentious note Tuesday ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"with Senate Democrats raising noisy objections","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that much of Kavanaugh 's lengthy paper trail is still off limits .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"The hearing proceeded","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"despite Democrats ' call for delay .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who control the Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"hope to confirm Kavanaugh in time","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"to join the high court","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"when its fall term begins next month ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"cementing a 5-4 conservative majority .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"At 53 , Kavanaugh would be the second-youngest member of the court and the second","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"appointed by President Trump .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"Sen. Chuck Grassley , R-Iowa ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"who chairs the Judiciary Committee ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"described Kavanaugh as one of the most qualified nominees","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"he has ever encountered .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"The Yale law school graduate has spent 12 years on the federal appeals court in Washington , D.C. ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"where he has authored hundreds of opinions .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"In his opening statement , Kavanaugh praised retired Justice Anthony Kennedy ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"for whom he once clerked","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and whose seat he would fill ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"as well as another judicial hero","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"- his mother .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"`` My mom taught me","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that judges do n't deal in abstract theories ;","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"they decide real cases for real people in the real world , ''","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Kavanaugh said .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"`` And she taught me","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that good judges must always stand in the shoes of others . ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Before Kavanaugh spoke Tuesday evening ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"the hearing was repeatedly interrupted by protesters .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"`` What we 've heard is the noise of democracy , ''","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"said Sen. Dick Durbin , D-Ill .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"In a statement Tuesday evening , the U.S. Capitol Police said","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"a total of 70 people were charged in connection with protests at Tuesday 's hearing .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Sen. Dianne Feinstein , D-Calif. , the top Democrat on the committee , warned","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that Kavanaugh would tilt the high court to the right , especially on hot-button issues such as abortion and gun control .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Politics","depth":2},{"id":40,"text":"Brett Kavanaugh 's Record On Abortion","depth":4},{"id":41,"text":"Brett Kavanaugh 's Record On Abortion","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"Listen · 5:08 5:08","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"`` The president","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"that nominated you","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"has said ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"' I will nominate someone","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"who is anti-choice and pro-gun . '","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"And we believe what he said , ''","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Feinstein said .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Feinstein was not reassured by Sen. Susan Collins , R-Maine ,","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"who said","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Kavanaugh told her","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"that the high court 's 1973 Roe v. Wade decision","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"legalizing abortion","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"is `` settled law . '","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"' `` The question is really do you believe","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"that it 's correct law , ''","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Feinstein said .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , scoffed at Democrats","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"who complained","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"that Kavanaugh is too partisan .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"`` You had a chance","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"and you lost , ''","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Graham said ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"referring to the 2016 presidential contest .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"`` If you want to pick judges from your way of thinking ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"then you better win an election . ''","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Trump also chimed in via Twitter ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"calling the hearings `` a display of how mean , angry , and despicable the other side is . ''","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Trump charged","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that Democrats `` will say anything ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and are only looking to inflict pain and embarrassment to one of the most highly renowned jurists","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"to ever appear before Congress . ''","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Kavanaugh himself , however , pushed back against the idea of the Supreme Court as a partisan institution .","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"`` The justices on the Supreme Court do not sit on opposite sides of an aisle , ''","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"`` If confirmed to the Supreme Court ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"I would be part of a Team of Nine ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"committed to deciding cases","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"according to the Constitution and laws of the United States . ''","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Democrats also complained","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"that the Trump administration blocked the release of more than 100,000 pages of documents","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"detailing Kavanaugh 's service in the George W. Bush White House .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Other documents were released at the last minute , or not at all","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"- including documents from 2003 to 2006","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"when Kavanaugh served as Bush 's staff secretary .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"`` There 's a 35-month black hole in your White House career","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"where we 've been denied access to any and all documents , ''","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Durbin said .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"`` During that period of time , President Bush was considering same-sex marriage","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"- an amendment","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"to ban it -","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"abortion , executive power , detainees , torture , Supreme Court nominees , warrantless wiretapping . '' `","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"` Before sitting on the bench ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"you were a political operative ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"involved in the most political and partisan controversies of our time , ''","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"added Sen. Patrick Leahy , D-Vt.","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"`` It is precisely those views","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"that are being hidden from us today . ''","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"`` I would think","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"that anyone","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"who wanted to sit on the nation 's highest court","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"would be proud of their record","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"and would want the American people to see it , ''","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"said Sen. Kamala Harris , D-Calif .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz , R-Texas , dismissed the complaints over missing documents as a distraction .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"`` There 's an old saying for trial lawyers :","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"If you have the facts ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"pound the facts .","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"If you have the law ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"pound the law .","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"If you have neither ,","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"pound the table .","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"We 're seeing a lot of table pounding this morning , ''","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Cruz said .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Sen. Mike Crapo , R-Idaho , agreed ,","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"calling Democrats ' complaints `` trumped up . ''","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"`` Their motives are clear , ''","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"Crapo said .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"`` Use any means available","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"to attempt to delay the confirmation process of a well-qualified jurist , fit for the job , indefinitely . ''","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"During his confirmation hearing for the appeals court in 2006 , Kavanaugh assured Durbin","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that he had not been involved in White House discussions of torture or the treatment of enemy combatants .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"NPR and the Washington Post later reported","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"that Kavanaugh was involved in those discussions ,","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"offering counsel on how those policies might be judged by the Supreme Court .","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"`` You are a committed textualist , Judge Kavanaugh , ''","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"Durbin said .","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"`` If you are going to hold others accountable for their words ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"you should be held accountable for your own words . ''","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"Although Kavanaugh helped to investigate then-President Bill Clinton","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"while working for independent counsel Kenneth Starr in the 1990s ,","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"he later wrote in a 2009 law review article","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"that presidents ' official duties are too demanding for them to be subject to such a probe .","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"`` I believe","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"it is vital","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"that the President be able to focus on his never-ending tasks with as few distractions as possible , ''","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"Kavanaugh wrote .","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"He suggested","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"that Congress excuse the president from both civil lawsuits and criminal investigations while in office .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"`` He does not believe","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"a sitting president should be investigated or prosecuted , ''","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"she told reporters on a conference call last week .","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"`` In other words , the president is above the law . ''","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"Democrats say","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Kavanaugh 's views on presidential immunity deserve special scrutiny now ,","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"given the ongoing investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election by special counsel Robert Mueller ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"which has already implicated a number of Trump associates .","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"`` This is a president","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"who has shown us consistently","depth":17},{"id":151,"text":"that he is contemptuous of the rule of law , ''","depth":17},{"id":152,"text":"Durbin said at Tuesday 's hearing ,","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"noting Trump 's firing of former FBI Director James Comey and his repeated criticism of Attorney General Jeff Sessions .","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"`` And it 's that president","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"who has decided","depth":17},{"id":156,"text":"you are his man .","depth":17},{"id":157,"text":"You 're the person","depth":16},{"id":158,"text":"he wants on the Supreme Court , ''","depth":16},{"id":159,"text":"Durbin said .","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"`` So are people nervous about this ?","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"Are they concerned about it ?","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"Of course they are . ''","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"`` We have to confront an uncomfortable but important question , ''","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"Sen. Chris Coons , D-Del. , added :","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"`` Whether President Trump may have selected you , Judge Kavanaugh , with an eye","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"towards protecting himself . ''","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"Two Republican members of the committee","depth":16},{"id":168,"text":"who often criticize the president","depth":16},{"id":169,"text":"agreed","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"that judicial independence is a particular concern in the Trump era ,","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"though they seemed less skeptical of Kavanaugh","depth":14},{"id":172,"text":"than did their Democratic colleagues .","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"Sens . Jeff Flake , R-Ariz. , and Ben Sasse , R-Neb. , both pointed to Trump 's tweet on Monday","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"criticizing the Justice Department over the indictments of two `` popular '' Republican lawmakers , just ahead of the midterms .","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"`` That is why a lot of people are concerned about this administration ,","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"and why they want to ensure","depth":15},{"id":177,"text":"that our institutions hold , ''","depth":15},{"id":178,"text":"Flake said .","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"`` The comments from the White House yesterday ,","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"trying to politicize the Department of Justice ,","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"they were wrong","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"and they should be condemned , ''","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"Sasse added .","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"`` And my guess is that Brett Kavanaugh would condemn them . ''","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"The testy exchanges Tuesday morning highlight Democrats ' lingering resentment over the treatment of former President Barack Obama 's last Supreme Court nominee , Judge Merrick Garland ,","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"who was never granted a hearing by Senate Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"Kavanaugh ,","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"who serves alongside Garland on the Court of Appeals for the D.C . Circuit ,","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"spoke highly of his colleague ,","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"describing Garland as `` superb '' in his opening statement .","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"Despite their concerns ,","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"Democrats have few tools","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"to block Kavanaugh 's path to the high court .","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"A rule change last year allows the Senate to confirm a Supreme Court nominee with a simple majority vote .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":389,"left":233,"right":388,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":0,"right":232,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":232,"left":205,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":199,"right":204,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":197,"right":198,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":1,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":203,"right":11,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":201,"right":202,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":200,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":206,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":222,"right":229,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},